<HEAD>Couple Has Third Holiday Baby</HEAD>
<DATELINE>INDIANOLA, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Some people celebrate April Fool's Day by playing pranks, <PERSON> St. </PERSON> <PERSON> Patrick </PERSON>'s Day with a toast to the Irish and Thanksgiving Day with a turkey. <PERSON> Sandy </PERSON> <PERSON> Moore </PERSON> has celebrated all three by having babies. Mrs. <PERSON> Moore </PERSON>, 33, of <LOCATION> Indiana </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Township </LOCATION> gave birth to <PERSON> Jason </PERSON>, 9 pounds, 1 ounce, on Thanksgiving Day in <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Penn </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hospital </LOCATION> in <LOCATION> Pittsburgh </LOCATION>. Mother and baby were doing fine. <PERSON> Jason </PERSON> is the third holiday baby for Mrs. <PERSON> Moore </PERSON> and her 33 year-old husband, <PERSON> Martin </PERSON>. Their oldest child, <PERSON> Amanda </PERSON>, arrived on April Fool's Day 1982, and their second child, <PERSON> Jacquelyn </PERSON>, was born in St. Patrick's Day 1984. Mrs. <PERSON> Moore </PERSON> attributes the birthdays to luck. `` All this has made me really happy,'' she said Monday night.
