ter variety of tastes than any previous picture. It has had practically no detractors _ even among those who do n't like <PERSON> Picasso </PERSON>. A picture by the French Impressionist <PERSON> Claude </PERSON> <PERSON> Monet </PERSON>, `` The Railroad Bridge at <LOCATION> Argenteuil </LOCATION>,'' sold for $ 12.55 million, also joining the list of the 10 most expensive works of art sold at auction. In June 28, another <ORGANIZATION> Monet </ORGANIZATION> painting, `` In the Field,'' sold at <ORGANIZATION> Sotheby </ORGANIZATION>'s in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION> for $ 24.90 million. Monday's auction of 60 works by 40 artists brought $ 102.01 million, a record for an Impressionist and modern art sale in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION>. Individual records were set for works by <PERSON> Picasso </PERSON>, <PERSON> Paul </PERSON> <PERSON> Gauguin </PERSON>, <PERSON> Alberto </PERSON> <PERSON> Giacometti </PERSON>, <PERSON> Paul </PERSON> <PERSON> Klee </PERSON> and <PERSON> Paul </PERSON> <PERSON> Signac </PERSON>.
