onference, told Tuesday's news conference <LOCATION> Moscow </LOCATION> is ready to include all its territory to the Urals in the new talks. He also said the Soviets are ready to accept Western suggestions that certain areas of <LOCATION> Turkey </LOCATION> be excluded from the talks. The issue of how much Turkish territory to include, and a <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> military base at <LOCATION> Adana </LOCATION> in southern <LOCATION> Turkey </LOCATION>, is one of the last major stumbling blocks to <ORGANIZATION> East-West </ORGANIZATION> agreement on a mandate. Both sides expect the dispute to be resolved.
