<HEAD>Valerie Harper Signs With CBS</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Valerie </PERSON> <PERSON> Harper </PERSON>, who left an <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> series in a contract dispute last year, will star in a new series on <ORGANIZATION> CBS </ORGANIZATION>, the network announced Tuesday. After <PERSON> Harper </PERSON> left `` <PERSON> Valerie </PERSON>,'' <PERSON> Sandy </PERSON> <PERSON> Duncan </PERSON> was brought in and the show renamed `` The <PERSON> Hogan </PERSON> Family.'' <PERSON> Harper </PERSON> sued <ORGANIZATION> Lorimar </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Productions </ORGANIZATION> and in September was awarded $ 1.85 million in damages and a share of the profits from the <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> show, of which she was part owner. Like `` <PERSON> Valerie </PERSON>,'' the <ORGANIZATION> CBS </ORGANIZATION> show will also be produced by <PERSON> Harper </PERSON>'s <ORGANIZATION> AV </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Productions </ORGANIZATION> and will be overseen by her producer husband, <PERSON> Tony </PERSON> <PERSON> Cacciotti </PERSON> It will be shot at <ORGANIZATION> MTM </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Productions </ORGANIZATION>, the site of the show that launched <PERSON> Harper </PERSON>'s career, `` The <PERSON> Mary </PERSON> <PERSON> Tyler </PERSON> <PERSON> Moore </PERSON> Show.'' <ORGANIZATION> MTM </ORGANIZATION> also produced the spinoff `` Rhoda,'' in which <PERSON> Harper </PERSON> starred. CBS did not yet have a title, premise or planned air date for the new series. The executive producer is <PERSON> Paul </PERSON> <PERSON> Haggis </PERSON>, who was responsible for the successful CBS sitcom `` One Day at a Time.''
