<HEAD>Witnesses Ready to Testify Against Most-Wanted Nazi War Criminal</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By TERRENCE PETTY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>BONN, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Nazi </ORGANIZATION> camp survivors are ready to testify against an elderly man alleged to be one of 10 most-wanted war criminals if <LOCATION> Argentina </LOCATION> upholds his extradition to <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION>, officials said Tuesday. West German prosecutors have issued an arrest warrant for former SS Capt. <PERSON> Josef </PERSON> <PERSON> Schwammberger </PERSON>, accused of killing thousands of people while he was commander of Nazi labor camps in <LOCATION> Poland </LOCATION> during World War II. An Argentine judge on Monday ordered that <PERSON> Schwammberger </PERSON>, arrested a year ago in a remote village, be extradited to <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Shwammberger </PERSON>'s lawyers say they will appeal the extradition order. <PERSON> Schwammberger </PERSON>, 76 has been a fugitive since he disappeared from a train in 1948 while being taken from <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION> to <LOCATION> American </LOCATION> military authorities in <LOCATION> Austria </LOCATION> to be tried, according to renowned Nazi hunter <PERSON> Simon </PERSON> <PERSON> Wiesenthal </PERSON>. Prosecutors allege the former SS commander was responsible for the deaths of more than 5,000 people, mostly Jews. Camp survivors have testified that he shot to death starving prisoners or set dogs on them. `` He was a sadist, an evil person,'' said <PERSON> Edward </PERSON> <PERSON> Blonder </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION>, who testified at a Argentine deportation hearing in July along with two other survivors of the <LOCATION> Przemysl </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Mielec </LOCATION> labor camps. <LOCATION> Stuttgart </LOCATION> prosecutor <PERSON> Helmut </PERSON> <PERSON> Krombacher </PERSON> said witnesses from two continents are expected to testify against <PERSON> Schwammberger </PERSON> if he goes to trial in <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION>. `` Testimony has b