sited him at Xavier in May 1987, two years after the <ORGANIZATION> CISPES </ORGANIZATION> probe ended, and wanted to know about <PERSON> Knitter </PERSON>'s reputation on campus and what he was teaching. <PERSON> Mike </PERSON> Lent of the <ORGANIZATION> CISPES </ORGANIZATION> national office said the group has gotten letters from contributors saying they would no longer donate money to the group because they were afraid their names would turn up in <ORGANIZATION> FBI </ORGANIZATION> files. Some private organizations `` have said they had concerns about working with us because of the fact we were under <ORGANIZATION> FBI </ORGANIZATION> investigation,'' said Lent. The suit said that although the investigation ended in 1985, information supporting the probe's validity was disseminated during a February 1988 appearance before the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Intelligence </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION> by the <ORGANIZATION> FBI </ORGANIZATION>'s <PERSON> Oliver </PERSON> <PERSON> Revell </PERSON>. The suit also said a newspaper article last June quoted Sessions as saying there had been a sufficient basis for the probe. In September, however, after an internal <ORGANIZATION> FBI </ORGANIZATION> review of how the probe was conducted, Sessions said the basis for the probe was information provided by an informant who proved to be unreliable.
