<BYLINE>By MICHAEL HOBBS</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>RALEIGH, N.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The roar of chain saws and the smell of pine from shattered trees permeated the air Tuesday as residents began putting their lives back together and cleaning up from an estimated $ 100 million in tornado damage. `` All my damage is minor compared to some of these people,'' said <PERSON> Jeff </PERSON> <PERSON> Johnston </PERSON> as he and his wife, <PERSON> Helen </PERSON>, began cleanup and repairs. Their house had broken windows and a piece of log embedded in the wall; a tool shed was destroyed. The <ORGANIZATION> Johnstons </ORGANIZATION>' next-door neighbors were worse off _ the side of their house was torn off. `` They'll have to move,'' <PERSON> Johnston </PERSON> said. `` This whole neighborhood is going to change a lot.'' Four people died, 157 were injured and about 850 were left homeless as the tornadoes tossed cars, houses and trees like playthings along a 200-mile stretch of eastern <LOCATION> North </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Carolina </LOCATION> early Monday. It was the first time since the state began keeping records in 1916 that tornadoes caused deaths in November, according to the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Climatic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Data </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Center </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Asheville </LOCATION>. Damage was estimated at $ 100 million statewide, according to the state public safety department. Raleigh alone suffered $ 75 million in damage, the city manager's office said. Teams from the <ORGANIZATION> Small </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Business </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Administration </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Emergency </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Management </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Agency </ORGANIZATION> fanned out Tuesday to calculate damage in all nine affected counties and determine what areas would be eligible for federal disaster aid. The dead were 12-year-old <PERSON> Edwin </PERSON> `` Pete'' <PERSON> Fulghum </PE