director, conducted the <ORGANIZATION> AGMA </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Chorus </ORGANIZATION> in `` Alleluia.'' Company members <PERSON> Tina </PERSON> <PERSON> LeBlanc </PERSON> and <PERSON> Glenn </PERSON> <PERSON> Edgerton </PERSON> danced the pas de deux from <ORGANIZATION> Joffrey </ORGANIZATION>'s 1973 `` Remembrances.'' <PERSON> Jodie </PERSON> <PERSON> Gates </PERSON> and <PERSON> Edgerton </PERSON> danced a pas de deux from `` Reflections'' by <PERSON> Gerald </PERSON> <PERSON> Arpino </PERSON>, the company's leading male dancer in 1956, now artistic director of the company. <PERSON> Joffrey </PERSON>, who was born in <LOCATION> Seattle </LOCATION>, died March 25 at 57.
