remark on possible resumption of ties with Washington. Picks up 8th
graf pvs, Genscher's good ... with minor editing to trim</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By DETLEF RUDEL</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>TEHRAN, Iran (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A government official indicated Tuesday that <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> is linking efforts to free foreign hostages in <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION> with the fate of Iranians believed held there. `` There are n't just American hostages in <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION>, but there also are Iranian hostages, who are in the hands of Christian militiamen,'' <PERSON> Mohammed </PERSON> <PERSON> Javad </PERSON> <PERSON> Larijani </PERSON>, <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION>'s deputy foreign minister, said. He made the comment after meeting with West German Foreign Minister <PERSON> Hans-Dietrich </PERSON> <PERSON> Genscher </PERSON>, whose three-day visit to <LOCATION> Tehran </LOCATION> was dominated by the hostage issue. <PERSON> Larijani </PERSON> was refering to three Iranians who disappeared with their Lebanese driver in 1982 and were presumed kidnapped by Christian Phalangist gunmen. The four are widely believed to have died. No group claimed responsibility for their kidnapping. `` Western nations, especially the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>, have close ties to -LRB- the Phalangists -RRB-,'' <PERSON> Larijani </PERSON> told reporters. `` We want all hostages to be free, the Iranians as well, and we will work as much as we can so that they are freed.'' He did not specify what actions <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> might take. In remarks quoted by the official <ORGANIZATION> Islamic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Republic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> News </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Agency </ORGANIZATION> and monitored in <LOCATION> Cyprus </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Larijani </PERSON> also did not rule out resuming ties with the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>. `` If one day we were to resume ties with the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> such a relationship would certainly be on the basis of mutual respect and non-interference in each other's affairs,'' he was quoted as saying. <PERSON> Genscher </PERSON> has offered to act as mediator in gaining the release of 14 foreign hostages, including nine Americans, believed held in <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION> by pro-Iranian Shiite Moslem extremists, West German government sources in <LOCATION> Bonn </LOCATION> said. <PERSON> Genscher </PERSON>'s good contacts with <LOCATION> Tehran </LOCATION> throughout the Iran-Iraq war were seen as key factors in the release of two West German hostages held in <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION>. Before ending his visit on Tuesday, <PERSON> Genscher </PERSON> told reporters he urged <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION>'s leaders to `` to use all possibilities toward contributing to the release of all hostages in <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION>.'' During his stay, <PERSON> Genscher </PERSON> held talks with <PERSON> Larijani </PERSON>, President <PERSON> Ali </PERSON> <PERSON> Khamenei </PERSON>, Foreign Minister <PERSON> Ali </PERSON> <PERSON> Akbar </PERSON> <PERSON> Velayati </PERSON> and other Iranian officials. <PERSON> Genscher </PERSON> said he raised the hostage issue in each of his discussions. In <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>, <ORGANIZATION> White </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Marlin </PERSON> <PERSON> Fitzwater </PERSON> said Tuesday that <PERSON> Genscher </PERSON> `` is not an emissary'' of the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> and is not representing the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> government in the discussions in <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION>. `` He is not speaking in our behalf,'' the spokesman said. `` Obviously we're interested to hear whatever comes up in these talks,'' <PERSON> Fitzwater </PERSON> said, adding that `` I'm not aware of any new hope'' for release of the American hostages. Longest held of the 14 hostages is <PERSON> Terry </PERSON> <PERSON> Anderson </PERSON>, 41, chief <LOCATION> Middle </LOCATION> <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> correspondent for <ORGANIZATION> The </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZ