<TEXT>
 Tornado-shocked victims tried to put their shattered lives and homes back in order today from a series of twisters that killed four people, including a couple found with their arms wrapped around each other. At least 17 tornado touch downs were reported early Monday, covering 200 miles of eastern <LOCATION> North </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Carolina </LOCATION>, injuring 151 people and causing more than $ 50 million in damage. One tornado sent one couple on a flying-mattress ride. <PERSON> Mark </PERSON> and <PERSON> Vera </PERSON> <PERSON> Cimerro </PERSON> landed on their mattress against a tree across the street. `` I held onto her as tight as I could, and the next thing I know, we are flying,'' said <PERSON> Cimerro </PERSON>. `` It was like a ride at the fair.''
