<HEAD>Florence Henderson and `The Brady Bunch' Celebrate Christmas</HEAD>
<NOTE>With LaserPhoto</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By JERRY BUCK</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Television Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 If <PERSON> Florence </PERSON> <PERSON> Henderson </PERSON> felt strange about seeing `` The Brady Bunch'' all grown up in the CBS reunion movie, so might viewers who are still hooked on reruns. `` The Brady Bunch'' are starting little bunches of their own, but they all got back together to celebrate Christmas in `` A Very Brady Christmas'' on Sunday. In addition to <PERSON> Henderson </PERSON>, back are <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Reed </PERSON> as father <PERSON> Mike </PERSON> <PERSON> Brady </PERSON>, <PERSON> Ann </PERSON> <PERSON> B. </PERSON> <PERSON> Davis </PERSON> as housekeeper <PERSON> Alice </PERSON>, and <PERSON> Maureen </PERSON> <PERSON> McCormick </PERSON>, Eve Plumb, <PERSON> Barry </PERSON> <PERSON> Williams </PERSON>, <PERSON> Christopher </PERSON> <PERSON> Knight </PERSON> and <PERSON> Mike </PERSON> <PERSON> Lookinland </PERSON> as the kids. Only <PERSON> Susan </PERSON> <PERSON> Olsen </PERSON> did not return for the two-hour movie, and the role of <PERSON> Cindy </PERSON> is played by <PERSON> Jennifer </PERSON> <PERSON> Runyon </PERSON>. `` It felt strange to go back to the roles,'' said <PERSON> Henderson </PERSON>. `` <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> and I were very nervous trying to get back into those characters. The kids are all grown. That's going to be quite a shock to all those kids who watch the reruns. `` The house has been redecorated. I'm into real estate now. <PERSON> Mike </PERSON>'s still an architect. One son's a doctor, one's a race car driver, one works in an office. One girl's married, one's married with a career and the youngest is in college. Plus, there are three grandchildren. Can you believe that? `` In the story <PERSON> Mike </PERSON> and I try to give each other surprise trips. I choose <LOCATION> Greece </LOCATION>, he chooses <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION>. Instead, we decide to bring all the kids home.'' `` The Brady Bunch'' was the kind of television project that the networks squeezed until they got everything out of it. The original series ran on <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> from 1969 to'74. From 1972 to'74, `` The Brady Kids'' was an animated Saturday morning show on <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION>. Next, it was a variety show, `` The Brady Bunch Hour,'' on <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> in 1977. Then, in 1981 NBC telecast the movie `` The Brady Girls Get Married,'' followed by a brief series called `` The Brady Brides.'' The Brady Kids also put out a musical album. `` It's amazing,'' said <PERSON> Henderson </PERSON>. `` Someone brought a ` Brady Bunch' lunch pail for me to sign. They'd been offered $ 800 for it. I do n't know why the <LOCATION> Bradys </LOCATION> keep coming back. I went to <LOCATION> Australia </LOCATION> and they're popular there. `` I guess it's because they're a family that gets along and works out its problems. I think people get some help from it. I know when I was a child, seeing movie musicals saved my life. I was the youngest of 10 and we were poor. I could go to the theater and forget my childhood problems. It gives people something to strive for.'' <PERSON> Henderson </PERSON>, who has four children, has been married for the past year to Dr. <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Kappas </PERSON>, a hypno-therapist. They live aboard a 70-foot yacht, The Big Flo, which is moored at <LOCATION> Marina </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Del </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Rey </LOCATION> when they're not cruising. She has her own show on the <LOCATION> Nashville </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Network </LOCATION>, `` Country Kitchen,'' and recently published a cookbook, `` A Little Cooking, a Little Talking and a Whole Lot of Fun.'' After the end of the `` Brady'' shows, she set a record for guest appearances on `` The Love Boat.'' She also was on an Afterschool Special and was a suspect on `` Murder, She Wrote.'' `` Working on a series forces you into a monastic way of life,'' she said. `` You work from early in the morning to late at night. I enjoyed it, but after the ` Bradys' I guess the right thing never came along. I do n't miss it.'' <PERSON> Henderson </PERSON> said that although she's the host of a cooking show, it's the guests who do the cooking. `` It's a comedy and country music show with cooking,'' she said. `` I'd started in country music so it was interesting to get back to my roots. When I grew up in <LOCATION> Indiana </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Kentucky </LOCATION>, that was the music we had at home. I sang with a country band in high school. We have as guests people like <PERSON> Willie </PERSON> <PERSON> Nelson </PERSON> and <LOCATION> Pearl </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bailey </LOCATION>. When you're cooking you can ask some pretty intimate questions.
</TEXT>
