SON> Mana </PERSON> <PERSON> Saeed </PERSON> <PERSON> Otaiba </PERSON>, the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Arab </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Emirates </LOCATION> minister, hinted at early trouble with the agreement. `` The ink is barely dry on the document and the <LOCATION> UAE </LOCATION> is indicating they intend to comply with it but they do n't consider it official. That would tend to diminish the importance of the agreement,'' said <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> Byers </PERSON>, senior energy analyst with <ORGANIZATION> Bear </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> , </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stearns </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; Co.
