<HEAD>Philip Morris Takeover of Kraft Clears Key Hurdle</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By SKIP WOLLENBERG</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Business Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Philip </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Morris </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Cos. </ORGANIZATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> says the federal government has cleared its $ 12.6 billion purchase of <ORGANIZATION> Kraft </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, a deal that would make it the world's biggest consumer products company The tobacco and foods giant said Monday that the <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Trade </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION> had declined to raise antitrust objections to the buyout. The lone remaining hurdle to the deal is obtaining sufficient shares under terms of <ORGANIZATION> Philip </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Morris </ORGANIZATION>' $ 106-a-share tender offer, which it reaffirmed would expire at 5 p.m. EST Friday. The company said about 49.8 percent of <PERSON> Kraft </PERSON>'s estimated 119.3 million common shares and share equivalents had been tendered as of last Friday, and analysts said they had little doubt the takeover would be completed. Previously, <PERSON> Philip </PERSON> <PERSON> Morris </PERSON> valued the transaction at about $ 13.1 billion, but said Monday that it had has found there were fewer common shares and equivalents outstanding than it had expected. Nonetheless, the acquisition still would be the biggest buyout to date outside the oil business. Only the $ 13.4 billion takeover of Gulf Oil by what now is <ORGANIZATION> Chevron </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> in 1984 was larger, and that could soon be surpassed as $ 20 billion-plus bids are being weighed for <ORGANIZATION> RJR </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nabisco </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Philip </PERSON> <PERSON> Morris </PERSON> said Monday the waiting period for the <ORGANIZATION> FTC </ORGANIZATION>'s review of the proposed takeover had expired on Friday Asked the significance of that development, <PERSON> Philip </PERSON> <PERSON> Morris </PERSON> spokesman <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> L. </PERSON> <PERSON> Knox </PERSON> said it meant the <ORGANIZATION> FTC </ORGANIZATION> had not challenged the deal. `` We can proceed with our tender offer,'' he said. Critics had argued that the size of the deal would hurt consumers by giving <PERSON> Philip </PERSON> <PERSON> Morris </PERSON> too much influence over prices, supply systems and advertising time. In <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>, <ORGANIZATION> FTC </ORGANIZATION> Director <PERSON> Anna </PERSON> <PERSON> Davis </PERSON> would neither confirm nor deny the <ORGANIZATION> Philip </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Morris </ORGANIZATION> statement. She said the commission had a policy of not commenting on such matters unless it blocked a merger or granted early termination of the required waiting period for antitrust review. In <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> trading, <PERSON> Kraft </PERSON> rose 62 -LCB- cents a share to $ 105.62 -LCB- and <ORGANIZATION> Philip </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Morris </ORGANIZATION> fell 37 -LCB- cents a share to $ 95.37 -LCB-. The <ORGANIZATION> Philip </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Morris </ORGANIZATION> deal would bring well-known <PERSON> Kraft </PERSON> brands such as Miracle Whip salad dressing, Velveeta cheese, Sealtest ice cream and Tombstone frozen pizzas into the same corporate corral as Marlboro cigarettes, <ORGANIZATION> Maxwell </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> coffee, <ORGANIZATION> Post </ORGANIZATION> cereals, <PERSON> Oscar </PERSON> <PERSON> Mayer </PERSON> meats and <PERSON> Miller </PERSON> beer. <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Goldman </PERSON>, who follows the food business for the securities firm <ORGANIZATION> Fahnestock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGA