<PERSON> Philip </PERSON> <PERSON> Morris </PERSON> had $ 27.7 billion in sales in 1987, while <PERSON> Kraft </PERSON> had revenues of $ 9.9 billion, giving the combined company a theoretical total of $ 37.6 billion.
