<HEAD>London Shares Slightly Firmer At Midday</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Share prices were slightly firmer in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION> at midday Tuesday with trading activity concentrated in a handful of the leading blue chip stocks, dealers said. The market was still recovering its confidence after Friday's announcement of a record 2.4 billion pound, or $ 4.5 billion, current account deficit for October and the subsequent rise in base lending raes to 13 percent, dealers said There were few economic developments Tuesday to give the market a firm direction, and trading was concentrated in a few stocks affected by special situations or takeover speculation, they said. The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index was up 4.5 points, or 0.25 percent, at 1,786.9 at 12:46 p.m., below the day's high of 1,793.5, up 12.0, which came soon after the market's official 9 a.m. Volume was a modest 263.2 million shares, up from 185.4 million shares at the same time Monday. `` The market is still picking up the pieces after Friday's trade figures,'' one dealer said. `` The market is cheap enough not to sell shares, but it's not cheap enough to generate much buying.''
