<HEAD>Coniston Extends $29-a-Share Offer to All of TW Service Shares</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 An investor group pursuing <ORGANIZATION> TW </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Services </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> said Tuesday its tender offer for some of <ORGANIZATION> TW </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Services </ORGANIZATION>' shares attracted about twice as many shares as sought and that it was extending its $ 29-a-share offer to all of the food services company's stock. The group, <ORGANIZATION> Coniston </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Partners </ORGANIZATION>, said its amended offer of $ 1.14 billion in cash for the 81 percent of <ORGANIZATION> TW </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Services </ORGANIZATION> that it does not already own would expire at 12:01 a.m. on Dec. 13. <ORGANIZATION> Coniston </ORGANIZATION> also said it had asked the <ORGANIZATION> Delaware </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Chancery </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> to require the TW Services board to redeem or invalidate the poison-pill rights that would otherwise make its bid for control of the company prohibitively expensive. In response, <ORGANIZATION> TW </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Services </ORGANIZATION> said its board would consider <ORGANIZATION> Coniston </ORGANIZATION>'s amended offer `` in due course. Its chairman and chief executive, <PERSON> Frank </PERSON> <PERSON> L. </PERSON> <PERSON> Salizzoni </PERSON>, said the substantial number of shares tendered was `` irrelevant'' because the partial tender was `` designed from the outset to stampede shareholders into tendering their stock in hopes of forcing the company into another transaction.'' He said the amended <ORGANIZATION> Coniston </ORGANIZATION> offer for all <ORGANIZATION> TW </ORGANIZATION> stock `` remains highly conditional.'' `` Given that it is conditioned, among other things, on <ORGANIZATION> TW </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Services </ORGANIZATION> entering into a satisfactory merger agreement, it remains merely an invitation to enter merger negotiations,'' he said in a statement. <ORGANIZATION> Coniston </ORGANIZATION>, a New York-based investment firm that already owns about 9.3 million of <ORGANIZATION> TW </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Services </ORGANIZATION>' 48.6 million shares, launched a tender offer for 15.75 million of <ORGANIZATION> TW </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Services </ORGANIZATION> shares in late October. The combination of those shares with what <ORGANIZATION> Coniston </ORGANIZATION> already owned would give it about 51 percent of the company. <ORGANIZATION> Coniston </ORGANIZATION> said that when its partial tender offer expired at 12:01 a.m. Tuesday, nearly 30.2 million shares had been tendered which would have given <ORGANIZATION> Coniston </ORGANIZATION> nearly 82 percent of <ORGANIZATION> TW </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Services </ORGANIZATION>' outstanding shares Under its two-step plan, <ORGANIZATION> Coniston </ORGANIZATION> said it would then acquire the remaining shares in a merger for $ 29 a share in cash. <ORGANIZATION> Coniston </ORGANIZATION> said the two-step plan was devised to get around the <LOCATION> Delaware </LOCATION> anti-takeover law that restricts uninvited bidders from building a stake in a company based in that state. <PERSON> Paul </PERSON> <PERSON> E. </PERSON> <PERSON> Tierney </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON>, a <ORGANIZATION> Coniston </ORGANIZATION> principal, said he expects the only obstacle that would prevent <ORGANIZATION> Coniston </ORGANIZATION> from buying tendered stock after its offer expires next month would be the poison pill. <ORGANIZATION> Coniston </ORGANIZATION> has said that if it acquires <ORGANIZATION> TW </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Services </ORGANIZATION>, it plans to sell the company's health services operations, which include 27 skilled nursing facilities and two retirement living centers. <ORGANIZATION> TW </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Services </ORGANIZATION>' other operations include 1,200 <PERSON> Denny </PERSON>'s restaurants, 400 <ORGANIZATION> Hardee </ORGANIZATION>'s fast-food restaurants and <ORGANIZATION> Canteen </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, a food services company.
