 <ORGANIZATION> Interco </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> said Tuesday that it had obtained definitive financing and was mailing the cash portion of the special dividends it had declared to ward off a $ 2.7 billion hostile takeover. As announced earlier, the special dividends for the restructuring and recapitalization amounted to $ 38.60 per share of <ORGANIZATION> Interco </ORGANIZATION> common stock. The company said checks in the amount of $ 14.221 per share were being mailed to shareholders of record as of the close of business on Oct. 13, and checks for $ 24.379 are being sent to shareholders of record as of the close of business on Nov. 22. <ORGANIZATION> Interco </ORGANIZATION> said it had been advised by the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> that shares of <ORGANIZATION> Interco </ORGANIZATION> common will trade `` ex-dividend'' with respect to the cash portions of the special dividends on Wednesday. The $ 2.8 billion <ORGANIZATION> Interco </ORGANIZATION> restructuring plan was valued by the company at $ 76 per share. <ORGANIZATION> Cardinal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Acquisition </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, headed by brothers <PERSON> Steven </PERSON> <PERSON> M. </PERSON> and <PERSON> Mitchell </PERSON> <PERSON> P. </PERSON> <PERSON> Rales </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> D.C. </LOCATION>, had mounted a $ 74-a-share takeover attempt but the hostile tender offer expired Nov. 16 and was not extended.
